title: For Sale:  DPMS Panther AP4 LR-308 + 9 Mags + Bipod + Sling (Caliber .308)
postcontent:
The Panther LR-308, earned the NRA Publication magazine "Shooting Illustrated" 2005 Golden Bullseye Award for Rifle of the Year. Again, in 2006, the Panther LR-308AP4 earned the NRA Publication's magazine "American Rifleman" Golden Bullseye Award for "Rifle of the Year".  

In order to meet the requirements for the Army's Semi-Automatic Sniper System (SASS), DPMS added a brass deflector to the new generation LR-308 and incorporated the now-familiar forward assist into the backside of the brass deflector. Unlike the AR-15/M16A2 design, the AP4 LR-308 forward assist engages the flat surface on the back of the enlarged bolt carrier rather than a series of cuts milled into the side of the carrier.

The AP4 LR-308's barrel is of 4140 chrome-moly steel.  Underneath the ribbed aluminum free-float handguard, however, the barrel has a heavy profile, measuring nearly an inch in diameter, which accounts for its famed accuracy.

In short, this is one very capable battle rifle with enough mags to fill up your tactical vest.  Included is the AP4; 9 Magazines; Bayonet Lug Bipod; and Sling (no ammo included).  Actual shipping charges via UPS from zip code 75801.  Payment can be by cleared personal check; postal money order; or paypal.  Enjoy!!!

title: For Sale:  Sold-Glock 19 Gen-3 Factory NiBX-Coating
postcontent:
KEELY ENTERPRISES
www.keelyarms.com

Glock 19 Gen-3 9mm w/ NiBX-coating

Available for purchase at our website:
http://www.keelyarms.com/ProductDetails.asp?ProductCode=g19%5Fnibx

We can also handle transfer paperwork for local pick-up
NO credit card fees!!

Brand new in box with 2-15 round mags. NiBX-Coating applied by manufacturer. The GLOCK 19 is ideal for a more versatile role because of its reduced dimensions when compared to the standard sized option. Chambered in 9x19, it has found worldwide acclaim with both private and public security agencies. In addition to being used as a conventional service pistol, it is ideal for concealed carry or as a backup weapon.


About the Technology
Why put Nickel Boron (NiB-X) on my Firearm?
NiB-X offers a unique combination of wear resistance and a low coefficient of friction (superb lubricity).  There are harder surface treatments available (but they have no lubricity) and there are more lubricious coatings (teflon scratches off) but there are no coatings that optimize this combination of performance attributes like NiB-X.  

Will the process affect my parts?
The NiB-X process does not affect the part through excessive temperatures like some other technologies you may consider.  And there is no hydrogen embrittlement of the part due to the process.  The maximum process temperature is 195F with an optional post coating precipitation bake to further harden the coating performed at 450F.  All temperatures are low enough as to not be detrimental to your parts.

What are the differences between NiB-X and other technologies such as Nickel Teflon, Chrome, Melonite (tennifer, black nitride), PVD (IonBond), Nickel boron nitride, and CeraKote (and other spray on bake on treatments such as DuraCoat, GunKote, etc).
NiB-X is harder than chrome and has a Rc70 hardness.  This is much harder than Nickel Teflon (~Rc45), and MeloniteTM  (Rc55).  The process temperature for Melonite and other salt bath nitrocarburizing is 1050F and too high for many components.  PVD coatings are harder than NiB-X but are only a couple microns thick and do not have the low coefficient of friction.  NIB-X provides higher reliability operation for longer durations and allows for reduced maintenance and easier clean up.  Nickel Boron nitride is essentially electroless nickel with boron nitride mixed in the matrix, very similar to the Nickel Teflon process.  Whereas NiB-X is a single coating and structure throughout the thickness, Nickel Teflon and Nickel Boron Nitride are duplex layers with a layer of electroless nickel and then a thin layer of EN+Teflon or EN+ Boron Nitride (.0001â€-.0002â€).  Once the telfon or boron nitride wears off you are down to only electroless nickel.

This is a very nice and very rare ac45 P-38.  This is a very nice late war Walther made P-38 and is much rarer than the common byf or cyq marked P-38's.  Any discerning collector knows that late war German pistols are hard to find and this one is a real gem.

This pistol has all matching numbers including the locking block.  The bore is mint and this pistol shoots great.  This pistol has the harder to find cog hammer.  Finish is close to 95% with the majority of the wear being on the front grip strap. This pistol is a WWII GI bringback and is not import marked and is completely original.

The original hardshell holster is in great shape and is waffenamt marked WaA938.  This pistol also comes with two original wartime magazines. One is WaA88 marked and the other is not waffenamt marked, but is a nice original wartime mag marked P-38v

I am asking $1,000.00 for this hard to find pistol with two magazines and original marked holster.  FTF in or around Newark, OH.  I will ship this pistol for an additional $50.00 upon receipt of certified funds.  lowball offers and disrespectful emails will be ignored.  I will trade for other military firearms.

title: For Sale:  Starr 1858 Double Action Revolver
location: Mt Orab Brown County, Cincinnati, Ohio
postcontent:
Great shape with some bluing Early production number of 262 matching numbers great bore. I can meet buyer at Eastgate for transaction.

The Starr revolver is an early development of the double action mechanism, it was a complicated but advanced design of the period, and generally made before the Civil War. It has two triggers which function as follows. Depress the forward trigger slightly and the rear trigger will become active, further depress the main trigger and the hammer will cock and hold in conventional single action manner. At this point the forward trigger is disengaged entirely, and single action firing is effected by depressing the rear trigger, or the cock can be slowly released by depressing the rear trigger and controlling the hammer back into resting position. Alternately the forward trigger can simply be operated from resting position without cocking, it will fire the round and advance the cylinder in one motion, hence the "double action". The revolvers are fitted with a single wood grip, another departure from the two grip convention of the period. Manufactured by Starr Arms Co , New York, NY. Frame is marked on right side, "STARR ARMS. CO. NEW. YORK.", and left side, "STARRS PATENT JAN 15, 1856." Serial number is marked on cylinder, and is visible on the frame with the hammer cocked. . title: For Sale:  Mossberg Maverick 88 12ga w/ extras, barely used.
postcontent:
This is a Maverick 88 12 gauge shotgun with an 18" barrel, no choke (open cylinder) and a five or six shot magazine tube- I think you can cram six 2 3/4" shells in there, but I've only ever loaded five, as that felt a bit more comfortable.

It is is very good condition. It has been taken out and fired once. Maybe 25 rounds of target shot and five rounds of buckshot through it.

I purchased this new from a local sporting goods store last year. I'm not sure if I have the original papers anymore (not much there except a couple brochures), but I do have the receipt to prove I am the original owner.

In addition to the shotgun, I'll include the soft case, which is nice and compact (fits the weapon nicely), the factory lock and keys, and twenty rounds of ammo. Ten Royal Buck #4's (21 pellet), ten Remington 7/8oz high velocity slugs.

I've compared this to multiple Mossberg 500's and can't find any difference besides the position of the safety. Unlike the earlier Mavericks, this one has the twin extractors and dual slides, same as the 500. Brass bead front sight.

The stock is the original; however, it has been shortened a little bit. Despite being over 6' tall with long arms, I just did not find the stock LOP comfortable.

It now has about 13", which is about an inch longer than the popular stocks advertised as either 'youth' or 'body armor.' The added shell carrier is tucked underneath the buttpad, firmly fixing it in place and keeping the shells out of the way of my right hand and cheek while in firing position. The light weight of the gun coupled with its compactness really makes it a great 'go-to' home defense shotgun.

Asking $250 OBO.
